Bún riêu 

1 lb ground pork
1/2 jar crab paste
1 pack of fried tofu puffs
1 pack of vermicelli (400g)
8 large tomatoes 
5 cloves garlic (divide in half)
1 lb crab/lobster meat
15 dried shrimp 
1 tsp ground pepper 

Green onions, mint, cilantro, peppers, and fried onions for garnish.

~Serves 6-8 people

1) On medium-high heat, add oil and cook half the minced garlic, dried shrimp and tomato wedges in a Dutch oven or large pot.
2) Fill the Dutch oven 3/4 full with water and allow to boil then simmer on low heat for 1-2 hours. 
3) In a large bowl, add ground pork, the remainder of the minced garlic, black pepper powder, eggs, and crab paste. Mix well. 
4) Follow package instructions to cook the vermicelli then set aside.
5) Use a large spoon to scoop the meat mixture to the pot of soup. Allow pot to boil then add fried tofu and crab/lobster meat. 
6) Add vermicelli to a bowl and assemble. Garnish with green onions and herbs of choice.

My friends and I are celebrating Lunar New Year by making Bánh Xèo - Sizzling (Happy) Crêpes. We picked up ingredients from @Freshcogrocery and had a lot of fun preparing this delicious meal. 

For the dipping sauce we got:
Garlic, Thai chili, sugar, rice vinegar, and fish sauce.

For the crêpes:
Dried mung beans, coconut milk, white rice flour, cornstarch, green onion, turmeric, and salt.

For the filling:
Olive oil, pork belly, shrimp, white onion, and bean sprouts.

For serving:
Lettuce, mint, basil, cilantro, carrots, and radish

I’ve put together 8 lucky dishes to eat during Lunar New Year:
1. Whole fish - surplus and abundance 
2. Shrimp - happiness and good fortune 
3. Dumplings - wealth 
4. Noodles - longevity 
5. Whole chicken - good luck and prosperity 
6. Spring rolls - wealth and prosperity 
7. Vegetables - energy and progress 
8. Tang yuan (glutinous rice balls) - togetherness and family reunion 

@freshcogrocery has everything you need to put together an effortless feast for your family that will blow them away. I got fish, shrimp, dumplings, hokkien noodles, roasted chicken, spring rolls, scallop, tang yuan, broccoli, carrots, shiitake mushrooms, ginger, garlic, green onion, lettuce, rice, Thai chili, cilantro, and tangerines. This feast looks like I put in a lot of effort but it actually requires minimal cooking. All I did is steam the fish, boil the shrimp, pan fry the dumplings, stir fry the noodles, buy a roasted chicken, warm up the spring rolls, steam the vegetables, and heat up the tang yuan on the stove. What will you cook for Lunar New Year?

One of my favourite ways to celebrate Lunar New Year is to invite my family over for hot pot! The boiling hot pot symbolizes a prosperous new year. I like to go all out when it comes to buying ingredients for hot pot. Luckily @Freshcogrocery has a wide variety of Asian ingredients needed for hot pot. I got radish, carrots, tofu, lotus roots, corn, mushrooms, Napa cabbage, lettuce, spinach, shrimp, scallop, beef/lamb slices, fish balls, udon noodles, minced garlic, soy sauce, and chili sauce! What are your must-have ingredients for hot pot?!

Almond flour banana bread - gluten free

Ingredients:
2 cups fine almond flour
3 overripe bananas
2 eggs
1 tbsp baking powder
1/2 tsp salt
1/2 tsp pure vanilla extract
1 handful of sliced kale (optional)

Grease or line a loaf pan. Preheat oven to 325 F. Stir all ingredients until smooth. Pour into the loaf pan. Bake for 50-55 minutes. 

Yes! I added kale instead of chocolate chips for a healthier option! I try to add some greens into everything I eat.

I made Mushroom Spinach Omelette using my new @hexclad pan! #hexcladcanada 

3 eggs
diced onions
sliced mushrooms
spinach 
shredded cheese

1. Whisk the eggs in a bowl. 
2. Add a bit of oil in a pan and cook the onion and mushrooms. 
3. Add the spinach and set aside.
4. Pour in the eggs and allow it to cook in low heat. 
5. Add the onion, mushrooms, and spinach back in on one side of the eggs then add the shredded cheese and flip.
